message.content:
Sally has 3 brothers and each of her brothers has 2 sisters. Since Sally is one of those sisters, we can count her as well when determining the number of sisters for each brother. Therefore, in total there are two sisters (one being Sally herself) per brother.

Since Sally has 3 brothers, she has:

3 brothers * 2 sisters each = 6 sisters

So, Sally has 6 sisters.
